Drawbacks (atAspectJ):

 - previleged aspects
 - intertype declarations
    
 Benefits of atAspectJ over (previous idioms):
 
  + Removal of the empty concrete aspect for static BT.
  + Adviceexecution idiom with @AspectJ is general for all kinds of advice
    + No need for explicitly define all pointucts, used in around advice, as named pointcuts.
    + No need for pointcut redefinition since '
  + No need to annotate/mark all around advice with a custom Java 5 annotation mechanism.